dc_title_s: LiDAR-Derived Countywide 1-m DEM (ft) for Buffalo County, WI 2016
dc_description_s: This data represents a LiDAR-derived countywide 1-m Digital Elevation Model (DEM) for Buffalo County, Wisconsin in 2016. This dataset is in WTM coordinates, EPSG 3071 with elevation in feet. A DEM represents the bare-Earth surface, removing all natural and built features.
dc_creator_sm: Wisconsin Department of Administration - Geographic Information Office
uw_supplemental_s: This lidar data dataset was created by the WisconsinView Partners (WVP) – the WI Department of Administration’s Geographic Information Office in collaboration with the UW-Madison Space Science and Engineering Center’s (SSEC) WisconsinView repository. Original lidar data in tiled format from federal or local county/city lidar projects were used to create countywide mosaics of datasets such as DEMS, Intensity images, and DSMs in various projections and coordinate systems. For detailed metadata please visit: https://web.s3.wisc.edu/wsco-wisconsinview/lidar/Buffalo/Buffalo_2016_3DEP_Delivery/Metadata/Metadata.zip
